Test Title: Verify export button opens export options
Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Content > List Documentaion Content
2-Click on export button
Description: Ensure that clicking on the Extract button displays export format options (PDF, XLS).
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List content page

Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Content > List Documentaion Content
2-Click on export button
3-Choose PDF
Description: Check that the system generates a PDF file containing the same data displayed in the content list.
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List content page
Expected Result: A PDF file should be downloaded showing the same data as the content list.
Actual Result: PDF file downloaded successfully and showed the same data in the content list
Comments: PDF generated successfully, and data matched

Steps:

Test Title: Verify that clicking the Search button performs the correct search action
Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Instructions  > List Documentation Content
2-Type keyword in the search field
3-Click on Search button
Description: Validate that entering a keyword filters the instruction list and shows only matching records
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List content page
Expected Result: Only instructions containing the search keyword should be displayed in the list
Actual Result:
The search results appear correctly while typing in the search field (live search works).
However, once the Search button is clicked, the system redirects to another unrelated page instead of showing filtered results
Comments: Search button in not working correctly

Test Title: Verify updating an content works correctly
Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Content > List Documentaion Content
2-Click on Update button
3-Modify one or more fields
4-Click on Update button
Description: Verify that when clicking the Edit icon, the existing content data is loaded into the Edit form so the user can update it correctly.
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List content page
Expected Result: The edit form should open with all fields pre-filled with the selected content record data, allowing the user to update the content.
Actual Result: Edit form loads data correctly for Active content, but shows empty form for Inactive content
Comments: Edit function works only for Active records. Inactive content data is not loaded, preventing updates. Logical bug in Edit functionality.

Preconditions:
